GC SMith 50 in 101 mins off 68 balls including 6 fours
100 up in 104 mins off 152 balls including 8 fours and a six
150 up in 153 mins off 230 balls including 10 fours and 2 sixes
5th Wicket 50 partnership in 42 mins off 70 balls including 2 fours and a six (Kallis 22, Rudolph 27)
JH Kallis 50 in 96 mins off 59 balls including 3 fours and a six
JH Kallis 50 in 96 mins off 59 balls including 3 fours and a six
JA Rudolph 50 in 62 mins off 60 balls including 6 fours
200 up in 177 mins off 264 balls including 18 fours and 2 sixes
5th Wicket 100 partnership in 65 mins off 104 balls including 10 fours and a six (Kallis 44, Rudolph 54)
250 up in 196 mins off 296 balls including 20 fours and 6 sixes
JH Kallis 100 in 130 mins off 89 balls including 5 fours and 5 sixes
5th Wicket 150 partnership in 86 mins off 136 balls including 12 fours and 5 sixes (Kallis 86, Rudolph 60)
5th wicket partnership for South Africa against West Indies beating the 98 between JH Kallis and JN Rhodes, Centurion 1998/99
5th wicket partnership for Newlands
West Indies Innings
Official Attendance : 20 000 (the capacity of the ground - thus a full house)
50 up in 107 mins 131 balls including 5 fours and a six
This is the largest margin of defeat by runs for the West Indies beating the 138 vs Pakistan at Sharjah in 1999/2000
This is the lowest total made by the West Indies beating their previous total of 87 vs Australia at Sydney in 1992/93
This is the largest margin of victory for South Africa beating their previous best of 208 vs Kenya at Newlands in 2001/02
This is the lowest total against South Africa beating the previous total of 98 by Sri Lanka at Colombo-RPS in 1993/94

milestones.description: South Africa's 210-run win against West Indies is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 208-run win against Kenya

stories.title: Windies bombed out for 54
stories.subTitle: South Africa v West Indies, 1st ODI, Cape Town
stories.summary: Jacques Kallis capped a phenomenal run of form with his fifth and most explosive century in consecutive internationals, to rescue South Africa's innings after a ponderous start to their one-day series against West Indies
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Andrew Miller
